20:24.098 --> 20:27.644
who could deal with this stuff, but...

20:29.979 --> 20:33.107
...you know, I-I'm not the girl
you booty-call sometimes

20:33.191 --> 20:37.070
because I'm great at relationships.

20:37.153 --> 20:39.781
I thought you were the one
booty-calling me.

20:41.783 --> 20:44.535
-Sorry, I didn't mean to...
-No.

20:44.619 --> 20:47.330
No, I'm sorry.

20:47.413 --> 20:50.166
About, uh, all of it.

20:57.674 --> 20:59.509
So how are you?

21:01.219 --> 21:03.221
I'm not gonna complain
about anything now, am I?

21:05.098 --> 21:06.474
Are we still gonna have sex?

21:08.017 --> 21:10.061
♪ ♪

21:39.424 --> 21:41.342
We're sorry. You have reached...

21:41.426 --> 21:42.927
Shit.

22:16.210 --> 22:18.921
♪ 'Cause now I'm even more lost ♪

22:19.005 --> 22:22.008
♪ It was a bad idea ♪

22:22.091 --> 22:23.509
♪ To think you were the one... ♪

22:23.593 --> 22:24.635
Hey.

22:24.719 --> 22:27.930
Can you turn the music down?

22:28.014 --> 22:30.349
-♪ 'Cause now everything's wrong... ♪

22:30.433 --> 22:31.851
Thank you.

22:32.977 --> 22:34.395
Um...

22:35.813 --> 22:39.358
So, my college reunion is next weekend.

22:40.693 --> 22:42.070
I've decided to go.

22:42.153 --> 22:44.030
Okay.

22:44.113 --> 22:46.324
Which means you're going.

22:46.407 --> 22:49.118
No. No. No way.

22:49.202 --> 22:50.953
Well, I can't leave you here by yourself.

22:51.037 --> 22:52.914
Okay, so I'll go to Sandra's.

22:52.997 --> 22:54.874
No, not while you're grounded.

22:56.334 --> 22:58.586
Come on, where's your sense of adventure?

22:58.669 --> 23:00.588
We've never taken
a real road trip together.

23:00.671 --> 23:02.882
You want to drive to New Orleans?

23:02.965 --> 23:04.842
We're gonna see
so much good stuff driving.

23:04.926 --> 23:06.177
I found this place in Arizona.

23:06.260 --> 23:07.512
-They got this, uh...
-Why are you suddenly

23:07.595 --> 23:09.472
so interested in seeing people
from college?

23:09.555 --> 23:11.891
Do you even talk to them anymore?

23:11.974 --> 23:13.267
That's not--

23:13.351 --> 23:14.936
The point is we're gonna reunite.

23:15.019 --> 23:16.562
It's a reunion.

23:16.646 --> 23:17.939
You're gonna know
a couple of people there.

23:18.022 --> 23:19.565
You know Guy.

23:19.649 --> 23:21.400
Dad, no one else is gonna bring their kid.

23:21.484 --> 23:23.486
It-It's weird. It's a weird thing to do.

23:23.569 --> 23:26.280
You know what?
I'm not gonna argue about this.

23:26.364 --> 23:27.657
Well, who's gonna feed Maurice?

23:27.740 --> 23:28.908
He's supposed to be low maintenance.

23:28.991 --> 23:30.076
That's why we got Maurice.

23:30.159 --> 23:32.703
Low doesn't mean none,
and we got him because I love him.

23:32.787 --> 23:35.081
I don't know. Ask Sandra.

23:38.876 --> 23:40.586
We're going.

23:40.670 --> 23:42.630
Fine. As long as you accept that

23:42.713 --> 23:45.383
I will be miserable the entire time.

23:49.595 --> 23:52.807
All right, I don't want you
to be miserable.

23:52.890 --> 23:55.434
I don't want to be miserable, so...

23:55.518 --> 23:58.563
if you promise to have
a good attitude about this...

23:59.814 --> 24:04.318
...I will teach you to drive on the way.

24:06.279 --> 24:08.739
"What, Dad?

24:08.823 --> 24:10.158
Could it be? For real?"

24:10.241 --> 24:11.534
"Yeah."

24:13.077 --> 24:14.954
Do we have a deal?

24:15.037 --> 24:16.914
♪ If you have a good attitude for real ♪

24:16.998 --> 24:18.541
♪ I'll let you get behind the wheel ♪

24:18.624 --> 24:22.670
If you promise
to never do that again, ever.

24:22.753 --> 24:25.047
♪ I will never, ever do it again ♪

24:25.131 --> 24:27.175
-♪ This is the last time I'm gonna do it ♪
-Dad.

24:28.467 --> 24:30.219
-♪ Very last time. ♪
-Get out.

24:31.804 --> 24:33.097
All right, good.

24:46.944 --> 24:49.405
-Is that it?
-Yeah.

24:49.488 --> 24:50.907
-You pack your retainer?
-Yep.

24:50.990 --> 24:52.450
-I didn't pay for braces so that...
-Yeah, I know.

24:52.533 --> 24:54.619
-I packed it.
-Where you going?

24:54.702 --> 24:56.787
I'm driving.

24:56.871 --> 24:58.247
Good one.

24:58.331 --> 25:00.291
What? But that was the deal.

25:00.374 --> 25:01.375
I'm driving till it's safe.

25:01.459 --> 25:03.211
I don't want you on the freeway yet.

25:03.294 --> 25:04.921
And I got reading material
to keep you occupied

25:05.004 --> 25:07.089
till it's your turn anyway.

25:07.173 --> 25:09.884
-College is over two years away, Dad.

25:09.967 --> 25:12.887
I don't know why I haven't had you
thinking about it for two years already.

25:12.970 --> 25:14.639
-Let's go!

25:21.812 --> 25:24.482
Jerry just needs to warm up.

25:24.565 --> 25:25.942
Right.

25:33.074 --> 25:34.617
How about journalism?

25:34.700 --> 25:36.702
I hate talking to strangers.

25:36.786 --> 25:38.579
-Medicine?
-Human body freaks me out.

25:38.663 --> 25:39.747
You know that.

25:40.790 --> 25:42.792
Why are you suddenly so obsessed
with my future?

25:45.378 --> 25:49.340
Don't your friends talk about
what they want to do for college?

25:49.423 --> 25:51.509
Glenn's gonna go to USC
because his dad went there,

25:51.592 --> 25:54.345
and Sandra's dream has always been
to be a fashion designer.

25:54.428 --> 25:56.514
I have no idea what I want to be.

25:56.597 --> 25:58.015
So what are you gonna do
after you graduate?

25:58.099 --> 26:00.017
Join a biker gang.

26:00.101 --> 26:01.978
Wally. Come on.

26:03.980 --> 26:05.815
Fine. I...

26:05.898 --> 26:08.401
-I want to see the world.
-You want to see the world?

26:08.484 --> 26:10.194
I could barely get you on this trip.

26:10.278 --> 26:12.571
I-I want more culture, okay?

26:12.655 --> 26:15.116
And you enrolling me
in traditional African dance classes

26:15.199 --> 26:16.367
when I was four doesn't count either.

26:16.450 --> 26:18.369
Thought I was doing the right thing.

26:18.452 --> 26:20.454
I was trying to teach you
both sides of yourself.

26:20.538 --> 26:22.832
No, that did not work.

26:22.915 --> 26:25.001
Okay, so where do you want to go?

26:27.128 --> 26:30.172
I was thinking of starting in the Balkans.

26:30.256 --> 26:31.507
Maybe Bosnia.

26:31.590 --> 26:32.883
Bosnia?

26:32.967 --> 26:35.052
That's your dream,
to go get swept up in a civil war?

26:35.136 --> 26:37.513
Oh, my God, Dad,
I'm pretty sure the war there

26:37.596 --> 26:39.140
literally ended before I was born.

26:39.223 --> 26:40.725
Wally, you are smart.

26:40.808 --> 26:43.686
You can't throw away your future.

26:43.769 --> 26:45.813
You-you got your whole life to travel.

26:45.896 --> 26:48.524
I don't believe that.

26:48.607 --> 26:51.610
People who play it safe when they're young
play it safe their whole lives.

27:00.745 --> 27:03.414
I think we're past
any crowded freeway traffic.

27:05.207 --> 27:07.043
We're not done talking about this.

27:09.837 --> 27:12.048
Don't do the eye thing.

27:14.175 --> 27:17.178
Wally, you have to drive at the same speed
as the flow of traffic.

27:17.261 --> 27:19.972
I know. That was, like,
question three on my permit test.

27:20.056 --> 27:21.474
Well, you're a snail.

27:21.557 --> 27:23.559
-All right. Okay.
-You're stressing me out.

27:23.642 --> 27:24.769
I'm stressing you out?

27:26.520 --> 27:27.980
You're not ready for multitasking.

27:28.064 --> 27:30.066
-The music just-- it calms me.
-Well, you need to speed up.

27:30.149 --> 27:31.359
-Fine.

27:31.442 --> 27:32.568
Hey, no! You need to slow down!

27:32.651 --> 27:33.778
-You just told me to speed up!
-Slow down!

27:33.861 --> 27:36.072
-Slow down!

27:37.698 --> 27:39.575
Oh, my God!

28:01.972 --> 28:04.600
♪ Feel the pain ♪

28:04.683 --> 28:07.228
♪ Very nice ♪

28:07.311 --> 28:09.897
♪ With the same ♪

28:09.980 --> 28:12.775
♪ Feeling good ♪

28:12.858 --> 28:15.236
♪ You'll leave there ♪

28:15.319 --> 28:18.072
♪ Show the map ♪

28:18.155 --> 28:20.741
♪ For the days ♪

28:20.825 --> 28:23.452
♪ Here before ♪

28:23.536 --> 28:26.122
-♪ Fall at best ♪
-♪ You're the same ♪

28:26.205 --> 28:28.707
-♪ You're a mess ♪
-♪ She, too ♪

28:28.791 --> 28:31.085
-♪ You a mess ♪
-♪ On the floor... ♪

28:31.168 --> 28:34.046
-- Need help?
-- No, I got it.

28:34.130 --> 28:36.799
-♪ Hold it tight ♪
-♪ Feel the pain... ♪

29:08.497 --> 29:10.499
♪ ♪

29:19.633 --> 29:20.968
What's going on over there?

29:21.051 --> 29:23.220
Nothing.

29:24.597 --> 29:25.764
Is it Glenn?

29:25.848 --> 29:27.850
Are you, um, are you getting good service?

29:27.933 --> 29:30.144
Because I-I have full bars,
but this thing--

29:30.227 --> 29:31.604
What are you doing?

29:31.687 --> 29:32.897
When you look back on this trip,

29:32.980 --> 29:34.899
I want you to remember
you and me spending time together,

29:34.982 --> 29:36.692
not you waiting
for your boyfriend to call.

29:36.775 --> 29:38.944
-All right?
-He's not my boyfriend.

29:39.028 --> 29:40.362
Did you guys break up?

29:40.446 --> 29:42.656
No, we can't break up.
We're not officially together.

29:42.740 --> 29:44.658
Wait, you've been seeing this guy
all summer,

29:44.742 --> 29:46.368
and he won't commit
to being your boyfriend?

29:46.452 --> 29:47.703
Who does this kid think he is?

29:47.786 --> 29:49.955
Dad, it's-it's not,
it's not like that, okay?

29:50.039 --> 29:51.582
Can I just-- can I have my phone back?

29:51.665 --> 29:53.167
No.

29:53.250 --> 29:54.835
But he hasn't texted me all day,

29:54.919 --> 29:57.922
and-and when he finally does,
I want to be able to talk to him.

30:01.675 --> 30:04.386
Get cleaned up.
Let's go check out the casino.

30:10.643 --> 30:11.977
♪ You know how to read my mind... ♪

30:12.061 --> 30:13.854
- Yeah, the odds are stacked
against the players.

30:13.938 --> 30:16.273
These machines-- they're all programmed
with these algorithms that make sure...

30:16.357 --> 30:17.775
I'm not an idiot, Dad, okay?

30:17.858 --> 30:20.528
I know it's unlikely you'll win big.

30:20.611 --> 30:22.321
But people are happy.

30:22.404 --> 30:23.989
It's the adrenaline.

30:24.073 --> 30:25.533
From the alcohol.

30:25.616 --> 30:27.701
Why do you think
they give out free drinks?

30:27.785 --> 30:29.828
They're free?

30:29.912 --> 30:31.413
You're missing the point.

30:31.497 --> 30:33.415
-No, you are.

30:33.499 --> 30:35.834
Look at them. They're having fun, okay?

30:35.918 --> 30:37.211
Yeah.

30:37.294 --> 30:39.255
Until they lose everything they came with

30:39.338 --> 30:43.467
and wake up
with matching snake eyes ass tattoos.

30:45.052 --> 30:47.346
You're nuts.

30:47.429 --> 30:48.847
Fine.

30:48.931 --> 30:50.975
Let's see how fun it can be
to lose some money.

30:51.058 --> 30:53.310
It's a ten dollar minimum bet,

30:53.394 --> 30:55.354
which means we have five chances.

30:55.437 --> 30:57.064
Assuming we lose.

30:57.147 --> 30:58.274
All right, where do you want to go first?

30:58.357 --> 31:00.234
Put one on red.

31:00.317 --> 31:02.152
Okay. Red.

31:08.492 --> 31:09.618
24 black.

31:09.702 --> 31:12.788
There went the cost of a movie ticket.

31:12.871 --> 31:14.540
Where to now?

31:14.623 --> 31:16.292
Do red again.

31:16.375 --> 31:18.210
Right.

31:18.294 --> 31:19.336
Red.

31:24.383 --> 31:26.385
26 black.

31:27.511 --> 31:30.639
One on black and one on even.

31:31.932 --> 31:34.018
Taking your bets up a notch.

31:34.101 --> 31:36.395
They say scared money never wins.

31:36.478 --> 31:38.105
You watch too much TV.

31:41.692 --> 31:43.777
25 red. Sorry.

31:46.697 --> 31:48.032
One bet left.

31:48.115 --> 31:49.575
-Where do we go?
-I don't care.

31:49.658 --> 31:51.535
This is rigged.

31:51.619 --> 31:54.455
All right.

31:54.538 --> 31:57.166
If I win, you give up Bosnia.

31:57.249 --> 31:59.293
Why would I agree to that?

31:59.376 --> 32:04.506
If I lose, I will at least hear you out
on your anti-college plans.

32:06.717 --> 32:08.719
-Okay. Okay.
-Yeah?

32:09.887 --> 32:11.388
♪ Do we have a deal ♪

32:11.472 --> 32:14.141
-♪ If you have a good attitude for real? ♪

32:14.224 --> 32:16.060
-Come on. Deal.
-Deal.

32:16.143 --> 32:18.520
-All right.

32:18.604 --> 32:21.148
-Easy.

32:21.231 --> 32:22.232
17 black.

32:33.952 --> 32:35.579
17 black.

32:35.663 --> 32:36.830
-Nicely done.
-- Oh, my God.

32:36.914 --> 32:38.374
-Holy shit. We won!
-Oh, my God!

32:38.457 --> 32:40.584
-Oh, my God, we won! We won!
-We won.

32:40.668 --> 32:41.794
-Oh, my God!
-Oh, my God.

32:41.877 --> 32:44.004
This never happens, okay?

32:44.088 --> 32:45.506
Highly improbable.

32:45.589 --> 32:47.675
Oh, my God. All right.

32:50.010 --> 32:51.970
I don't know if I'm more excited
about the $350

32:52.054 --> 32:55.265
or the fact that you're not gonna get
kidnapped in the Balkans.

32:55.349 --> 32:57.393
Oh, well, you only ruled out one country.

32:57.476 --> 33:00.104
I still have Kosovo and Serbia.

33:00.187 --> 33:02.523
-You cheater. You're a cheater.

33:02.606 --> 33:04.566
What's on tap next?

33:04.650 --> 33:06.568
We're going back to the hotel.

33:06.652 --> 33:07.903
Are-are you insane? We-we can't stop now.

33:07.986 --> 33:09.279
We're on a winning streak.

33:09.363 --> 33:12.825
Not knowing when to stop
is how people lose everything.

33:12.908 --> 33:16.203
So keep the 50 you started with,
and at worst we'll end up even.

33:16.286 --> 33:20.958
Or we take it all and invest it
in a retirement fund for you.

33:25.003 --> 33:27.589
And suddenly you're you again.

33:27.673 --> 33:30.050
♪ ♪

33:35.139 --> 33:36.724
Take it easy.

33:38.684 --> 33:40.185
You got this.

33:40.269 --> 33:42.062
-Oh!

33:42.146 --> 33:44.273
-- Ah, there's too many cars.

33:44.356 --> 33:45.441
I-I can't get in.

33:45.524 --> 33:47.818
You just need to commit and do it.

33:47.901 --> 33:49.987
-Okay. Oh. Oh. -No.

33:50.070 --> 33:51.613
Oh.

33:57.870 --> 33:59.788
Hell yeah!

33:59.872 --> 34:02.166
-Okay.

34:09.757 --> 34:11.550
Don't even think about it.

34:11.633 --> 34:13.594
-What if it's Glenn?
-What if it is?

34:13.677 --> 34:16.180
You know, I haven't heard from him
in, like, over a day, so--

34:16.263 --> 34:18.223
-What are you doing?
-Look at that. He's alive.

34:22.686 --> 34:24.062
Will you read it?

34:24.146 --> 34:26.523
If it looks like you shouldn't see it,
then just stop.

34:26.607 --> 34:27.691
I don't like this idea.

34:27.775 --> 34:29.860
Well, if we had a normal, modern car,

34:29.943 --> 34:31.695
the console would automatically
read the message

34:31.779 --> 34:33.363
and we wouldn't be having
this conversation right now.

34:33.447 --> 34:35.240
You used to like vintage things.

34:35.324 --> 34:37.826
Dad, what if he's telling me he, like,
lost a limb or something?

34:37.951 --> 34:40.788
It-it would be rude of me not to respond.

34:47.127 --> 34:48.879
"Hey, babe.

34:49.880 --> 34:52.132
"Sorry I missed"--

34:52.216 --> 34:53.801
that's spelled M-I-S-T--

34:53.884 --> 34:56.303
"you yesterday.

34:56.386 --> 34:58.847
I was at the becah"--

34:58.931 --> 35:00.682
I think he means "beach"--

35:00.766 --> 35:03.811
"with Zac n Amy

35:03.894 --> 35:06.313
n my phone died."

35:06.396 --> 35:07.606
He really can't spell "missed"?

35:07.689 --> 35:08.982
Even with autocorrect?

35:09.066 --> 35:10.651
He turned off autocorrect.

35:10.734 --> 35:15.280
He says he doesn't like his phone
telling him what to do or-or say or think.

35:15.364 --> 35:16.698
Amy's his ex. Why would he go with her?

35:16.782 --> 35:18.325
And why would he tell me?

35:18.408 --> 35:20.619
-Maybe it's another Amy.
-There's no other Amy.

35:20.702 --> 35:22.329
-There's only one Amy?
-Will you text him back?

35:22.412 --> 35:24.957
-No, I don't...
-Just write: "Call you later."

35:26.792 --> 35:30.420
All right, is that, uh,
"you" with the traditional spelling or...

35:30.504 --> 35:32.756
-Shit.

35:35.425 --> 35:38.095
-How fast are you going?
-44?

35:38.178 --> 35:39.555
You should be going 65.

35:39.638 --> 35:40.848
-Well, it feels like I'm going a hundred!
-All right.

35:40.931 --> 35:42.182
When it's safe,
pull over to the right lane.

35:42.266 --> 35:45.352
-Okay, look before you change lanes!
-Uh...

35:45.435 --> 35:47.312
I did look! I didn't see him!

35:47.396 --> 35:48.397
Uh...

35:48.480 --> 35:49.481
All right. You're clear.

35:49.565 --> 35:50.566
-Go now.
-Oh, no, no.

35:50.649 --> 35:52.067
Someone is just gonna sneak up again.

35:52.150 --> 35:53.527
-I'm not gonna let someone hit you.

35:53.610 --> 35:55.362
Go ahead. You're clear.

35:58.115 --> 35:59.366
-Did you close your eyes?!
-Yeah!

35:59.449 --> 36:01.118
-I was too scared to look!
-No! No!

36:01.201 --> 36:02.911
You do not close your eyes on the road

36:02.995 --> 36:04.913
-ever under any circumstances!
-Okay, geez!

36:04.997 --> 36:06.164
You always keep your eyes open!

36:06.248 --> 36:07.416
I-- It was like one second, okay?

36:07.499 --> 36:09.710
All right, that is,
that is the first rule.

36:09.793 --> 36:11.587
You cannot close your eyes!

36:11.670 --> 36:13.088
You have to look!

36:32.399 --> 36:35.736
♪ I am a passenger ♪

36:35.819 --> 36:39.907
♪ And I ride and I ride ♪

36:39.990 --> 36:42.868
--♪ I ride through
the city's backsides... ♪

36:42.951 --> 36:44.870
I didn't know you knew this song.

36:44.953 --> 36:46.747
You think you know The Stooges
and I don't?

36:46.830 --> 36:48.790
This is Iggy, actually, solo.

36:50.334 --> 36:52.252
Who are you?

36:52.336 --> 36:54.421
I always thought you listened
to, like, smooth jazz.

36:54.504 --> 36:56.673
Sometimes.

36:56.757 --> 36:59.134
-Jazz is cool.

37:01.261 --> 37:05.349
♪ I am the passenger ♪

37:05.432 --> 37:07.559
♪ I stay under glass ♪

37:08.810 --> 37:11.563
♪ I look through my window so bright ♪

37:11.647 --> 37:15.776
♪ I see the stars come out tonight ♪

37:15.859 --> 37:19.321
♪ I see the bright and hollow sky ♪

37:19.404 --> 37:22.532
♪ Over the city's ripping sky ♪

37:22.616 --> 37:26.411
♪ And everything looks good tonight... ♪

37:26.495 --> 37:27.704
I don't know any athletes.

37:27.788 --> 37:28.789
This better be a really...

37:28.872 --> 37:29.873
He's a very famous athlete.

37:29.957 --> 37:30.999
Uh, football player?

37:31.083 --> 37:32.501
-- No.
-- Um, basketball player?

37:32.584 --> 37:33.585
No.

37:33.669 --> 37:34.920
-Baseball?
-No.

37:35.003 --> 37:36.338
Soccer?

37:36.421 --> 37:37.714
No.

37:37.798 --> 37:39.174
-Tennis?
-No.

37:39.257 --> 37:40.550
Lacrosse?

37:40.634 --> 37:43.387
I'll give this to you if you can name
one famous lacrosse player.

37:46.390 --> 37:50.519
