37:50.602 --> 37:54.648
♪ La, la, la, la, la-la-la-la ♪

37:54.731 --> 37:55.816
-♪ La, la, la, la... ♪

38:06.702 --> 38:08.453
Should we ring the bell again?

38:09.579 --> 38:11.581
Let's give it a minute.

38:17.462 --> 38:18.547
You okay?

38:18.630 --> 38:21.550
With, uh, whatever you're...

38:21.633 --> 38:22.926
You wouldn't get it.

38:23.010 --> 38:24.177
Why not?

38:26.930 --> 38:29.307
When's the last time you went on a date?

38:31.768 --> 38:34.479
More recently than you think.

38:34.563 --> 38:35.689
-Wow, okay.

38:35.772 --> 38:37.941
At least you're finally copping to it.

38:38.984 --> 38:40.152
You've known?

38:40.235 --> 38:43.113
All those nonspecific work dinners?
Really?

38:44.865 --> 38:46.908
Wh... Why didn't you ever say anything?

38:46.992 --> 38:48.744
Why didn't you?

38:53.248 --> 38:55.917
Has anyone been serious?

38:57.586 --> 39:00.464
-Stop. Come on.

39:01.506 --> 39:02.966
Um...

39:06.428 --> 39:10.766
I was kind of seeing this woman, uh...

39:10.849 --> 39:12.184
Annie.

39:12.267 --> 39:13.685
Um...

39:14.936 --> 39:16.563
But it wasn't...

39:18.315 --> 39:20.317
She's younger. Um...

39:22.778 --> 39:26.490
And we're at, uh,
different places in our lives.

39:26.573 --> 39:28.116
Does she know you feel that way?

39:30.619 --> 39:34.122
Oh. I'm sorry for the wait.

39:34.206 --> 39:35.624
Nice hat.

39:35.707 --> 39:38.919
Yeah. Uh, my-my dad wanted souvenirs.

39:39.002 --> 39:43.131
Ah, well, nothing says Texas
like a big-ass sombrero, does it?

39:44.674 --> 39:45.967
Y'all need a room?

39:47.010 --> 39:48.011
Yeah.

39:48.095 --> 39:50.472
-Okay.

40:06.363 --> 40:07.697
I'm gonna get some ice.

40:07.781 --> 40:09.616
-I'll be right back, okay?

40:22.754 --> 40:24.089
ANNIE
Hey, this is Annie.

40:24.172 --> 40:26.591
-Leave a message.

40:26.675 --> 40:28.760
Hey, it's Max.

40:28.844 --> 40:30.887
I don't know why I said my name just now.

40:30.971 --> 40:33.181
Um, you know who it is.

40:33.265 --> 40:37.435
'Cause of my voice
and, um, caller I.D., clearly.

40:37.519 --> 40:41.690
On my way to New Orleans with, uh, Wally

40:41.773 --> 40:45.402
for my college reunion.

40:45.485 --> 40:48.530
Turns out Wally's not the most,
uh, ready to drive.

40:50.157 --> 40:54.953
So, uh, hopefully, this wasn't
the worst idea in the world.

40:55.036 --> 40:59.541
Uh, anyway, I was, uh,
just, uh, calling to...

41:01.585 --> 41:04.379
...because I've been thinking about you.

41:06.256 --> 41:11.136
I guess I had thought
that maybe there could be

41:11.219 --> 41:13.305
more between us.

41:13.388 --> 41:17.100
Which is stupid, obviously,
given everything.

41:17.184 --> 41:18.643
Um...

41:18.727 --> 41:21.479
Anyway, now I'm rambling.

41:21.563 --> 41:25.442
Uh, all right, I'm gonna take
a sleeping pill and call it a night.

41:30.030 --> 41:32.616
♪ ♪

42:08.151 --> 42:10.153
♪ ♪

43:04.374 --> 43:06.001
Later, Colton!

43:06.084 --> 43:08.003
Hey, did it cause problems?

43:08.086 --> 43:09.629
-Everyone ready?
-Been waiting for you

43:09.713 --> 43:11.047
to get your late ass out here.

43:11.131 --> 43:12.382
- Looks like you found a way
to fill the time.

43:12.465 --> 43:13.466
You are always late, bro.

43:13.550 --> 43:14.634
Sorry, some of us have jobs.

43:14.718 --> 43:17.345
Oh, a'ight.

43:30.734 --> 43:31.943
Uh...

43:33.486 --> 43:34.696
One-one sec.

43:37.365 --> 43:39.367
♪ ♪

43:41.453 --> 43:43.455
♪ I was a lone wolf ♪

43:46.791 --> 43:48.209
♪ I thought I lost my pack... ♪

43:48.293 --> 43:51.254
You know, you look pretty different
without that sombrero.

43:51.338 --> 43:53.423
That's probably a good thing.

43:53.506 --> 43:55.383
You got a good head for it.

43:56.426 --> 43:57.844
Thanks?

43:57.927 --> 44:00.513
You're not 21, are you?

44:00.597 --> 44:02.807
18. Why?

44:06.853 --> 44:08.355
There's another one.

44:13.902 --> 44:15.779
Y'all, we going to a party or not?

44:15.862 --> 44:18.406
I didn't put on my makeup
to stand around in a parking lot.

44:18.490 --> 44:19.783
Yeah, let's roll.

44:19.866 --> 44:20.909
Shotgun.

44:20.992 --> 44:22.911
You want to come with?

44:23.953 --> 44:26.247
-Oh, no, no. I-I can't. I actually...
-Come on.

44:26.331 --> 44:29.334
How many times you get to see shooting
stars in the middle of nowhere Texas?

44:32.545 --> 44:34.381
Hop in. Come on.

45:00.490 --> 45:02.283
-- ...20, 21,

45:02.367 --> 45:04.411
22, 23,

45:04.494 --> 45:08.164
24, 25, 26...

45:08.248 --> 45:10.041
-Let's go!

45:14.796 --> 45:17.215
-That's how it's done!
-Hey, stop your bragging, bro.

45:17.298 --> 45:20.009
-Who's next?
-Uh...

45:20.093 --> 45:21.970
New girl.

45:26.391 --> 45:28.226
-Um...
-- Come on.

45:28.309 --> 45:29.727
-Okay.
-Cool.

45:31.396 --> 45:32.689
Get her up.

45:32.772 --> 45:34.274
All right, ready?

45:36.067 --> 45:38.236
Here you go. All right, and...

45:38.319 --> 45:41.197
One, two, three,

45:41.281 --> 45:44.325
four, five, six,

45:44.409 --> 45:45.910
-seven, eight, nine...

45:45.994 --> 45:47.454
No.

45:48.955 --> 45:50.498
-- Oh!

45:50.582 --> 45:51.958
You okay?

45:52.041 --> 45:53.293
I'm a little dizzy.

45:53.376 --> 45:55.545
Um, I-I think the blood
just rushed to my head.

45:55.628 --> 45:57.714
Um...

45:57.797 --> 46:00.091
-Sorry.
-Ooh!

46:06.014 --> 46:07.765
Yo, Wally.

46:07.849 --> 46:10.351
Want to hear a secret?

46:10.435 --> 46:12.353
-Rusty lost his virginity here.
-- Don't...

46:12.437 --> 46:13.730
-Shut up.

46:13.813 --> 46:15.356
It was, like, literally right over there.

46:15.440 --> 46:16.691
Thank you, Jen.

46:16.774 --> 46:19.360
Uh, sounds romantic.

46:19.444 --> 46:21.362
-Ha-ha. -Mm.

46:22.697 --> 46:24.908
MAN
Yeah, there it is!

46:27.035 --> 46:28.578
Hey, what's up, partner?

46:28.661 --> 46:30.121
-You ready?
-Flip cup?

46:30.205 --> 46:32.957
You already know.
I got to defend my title.

46:33.041 --> 46:35.460
-We'll see about that.
-What you talking about?

46:49.974 --> 46:51.476
Want a nicer view?

46:51.559 --> 46:53.561
♪ ♪

46:59.859 --> 47:01.986
♪ Can the dark side ♪

47:02.070 --> 47:06.074
♪ Light my way out? ♪

47:06.157 --> 47:07.325
♪ Yeah, yeah ♪

47:07.408 --> 47:08.826
That's so cool.

47:08.910 --> 47:13.790
♪ Lay your hand across my face ♪

47:13.873 --> 47:15.500
♪ Yeah, yeah... ♪

47:15.583 --> 47:17.502
How'd you get that scar on your eyebrow?

47:17.585 --> 47:19.671
Oh. Uh...

47:19.754 --> 47:21.297
I wish it was a cool story.

47:21.381 --> 47:24.217
Tell me anyway.

47:25.718 --> 47:27.929
Um, when I was three,

47:28.012 --> 47:32.225
my-my dad wanted to take me
to the beach for the first time,

47:32.308 --> 47:34.102
and he put way too much sunscreen on me.

47:35.311 --> 47:39.566
I slipped out of his hands and hit my head
on the corner of the coffee table.

47:39.649 --> 47:41.526
Well, at least he was trying
to protect you from the sun.

47:41.609 --> 47:44.404
-He said my eyebrow split open
like a mouth. -Ooh.

47:44.487 --> 47:46.406
So, yeah, we did not go
to the beach that day.

47:48.157 --> 47:52.912
But he, uh, he always overcompensates
and tries to bring me now.

47:57.917 --> 48:00.420
I guess I should say I got it
fighting crime or something.

48:00.503 --> 48:03.339
You know, actually I hated it
when I was a kid,

48:03.423 --> 48:05.341
but, um, I-I like it now.

48:05.425 --> 48:06.968
I mean, I don't, I don't like it.

48:07.051 --> 48:10.555
I just-- I don't hate it
as much as I used to.

48:10.638 --> 48:12.223
You should like it.

48:12.307 --> 48:13.891
It's cute.

48:20.023 --> 48:22.942
You sure you don't want to be down there
with your friends?

48:23.026 --> 48:25.486
It's way better up here.

48:33.661 --> 48:34.829
Uh...

48:34.912 --> 48:36.039
-Oh.
-Um...

48:36.122 --> 48:37.498
Oh, no.

48:37.582 --> 48:39.125
-Um...
-No, no, it's...

48:39.208 --> 48:40.877
You're great.

48:40.960 --> 48:42.211
It's just...

48:42.295 --> 48:44.297
Actually, there's this girl.

48:45.548 --> 48:47.842
She's off at college.

48:47.925 --> 48:52.472
I guess, when I'm drinking,
I get a little flirty sometimes.

48:54.057 --> 48:56.768
Can we just pretend like
that didn't happen?

49:01.272 --> 49:03.066
I'm probably gonna marry her one day.

49:03.149 --> 49:05.401
If I ever get my shit together.

49:06.527 --> 49:08.154
I'm sorry. I-I didn't mean to lead you on
or anything.

49:08.237 --> 49:10.657
No, no, it's, um...

49:10.740 --> 49:12.784
it's okay.

49:12.867 --> 49:17.080
♪ Life is too short ♪

49:17.163 --> 49:20.958
♪ But I will live for you ♪

49:21.042 --> 49:22.669
♪ You're mucking... ♪

49:42.980 --> 49:45.274
All right, Wally, up and at 'em.

49:55.827 --> 49:57.745
ANNIE
Hey, it's Annie.

49:57.829 --> 50:00.540
I'm saying my name 'cause you did.

50:00.623 --> 50:04.127
Anyway, I just wanted to say that, uh,

50:04.210 --> 50:06.587
it wasn't stupid.

50:06.671 --> 50:08.464
I've been thinking about you, too.

50:08.548 --> 50:10.633
So...

50:10.717 --> 50:12.301
call me back.

50:20.268 --> 50:22.562
Come on, Wally.

50:22.645 --> 50:24.272
It's a shared bathroom.

50:24.355 --> 50:26.190
Let's get moving.

50:27.191 --> 50:28.651
Honey?

50:35.116 --> 50:36.576
Wally?

50:55.636 --> 50:57.722
WALLY
It's Wally. Speak if you want.

50:58.890 --> 51:01.184
Hey. Where are you?

51:05.188 --> 51:06.606
WALLY
It's Wally. Speak if you want.

51:07.899 --> 51:09.692
Wally, can you call me back, please?

51:09.776 --> 51:11.027
-Thank you.

51:11.110 --> 51:13.863
Have you seen a teenage girl
anywhere walking around?

51:13.946 --> 51:15.239
Hello?

51:15.323 --> 51:16.449
Hi.

51:16.532 --> 51:17.784
Oh.

51:17.867 --> 51:20.161
Have you seen a young girl
around here anywhere?

51:21.204 --> 51:23.039
Uh...

51:23.122 --> 51:24.499
No, sir.

51:24.582 --> 51:26.083
Do you know of a place
where a kid might wander off to?

51:26.167 --> 51:27.960
She know anyone out here?

51:28.044 --> 51:29.712
No. Why?

51:29.796 --> 51:31.964
Well, there was a big party last night.

51:32.048 --> 51:33.841
I would've been there if I wasn't working.

51:33.925 --> 51:35.092
Where?

51:35.176 --> 51:37.553
Uh, Old Man Baker's farm.

51:37.637 --> 51:38.805
-Old Man Baker?
-Yeah.

51:38.888 --> 51:41.015
He always calls the cops on us,

51:41.098 --> 51:43.142
but he's got like 400 acres,
so what does he care

51:43.226 --> 51:45.937
if we get wasted in the way
back of his land, you know?

51:46.020 --> 51:48.856
Where is it? Where's, wh-where's the farm?

51:48.940 --> 51:50.483
Would this help?

51:50.566 --> 51:51.859
Oh, my God, sir.

51:51.943 --> 51:54.153
Uh, I can give you...

51:54.237 --> 51:56.155
♪ ♪

52:18.261 --> 52:20.263
♪ ♪

52:36.153 --> 52:37.280
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

52:37.363 --> 52:38.906
What... what time is it?

52:38.990 --> 52:40.825
I-I, um, I have to get back.

52:42.368 --> 52:43.953
Did Baker call the cops again?

52:44.036 --> 52:45.997
No, it's-it's... it's firemen.

52:46.080 --> 52:47.164
Jesus.

52:47.248 --> 52:48.583
Don't they have anything better to do?

52:48.666 --> 52:50.084
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

52:50.167 --> 52:51.711
-Shit, shit, shit. I'm dead.
-Well...

52:53.212 --> 52:54.964
...looks like you got a ride.

53:01.971 --> 53:03.639
Wally?

53:03.723 --> 53:05.266
Wally, what are you doing up there?

53:05.349 --> 53:06.726
What the hell were you thinking?!

53:06.809 --> 53:08.728
-I'm sorry, sir. It's my fault.
-What did you do to her?!

53:08.811 --> 53:10.479
-I did nothing, nothing. I didn't do...
-Dad, he didn't do anything, okay?

53:10.563 --> 53:13.107
-Don't lie to me. Don't-don't-- just...
-I'm not. I'm not.

53:13.190 --> 53:15.401
I tried to text you,
b-but my phone died and-and...

53:15.484 --> 53:16.819
That's what you have to say?!

53:16.903 --> 53:18.404
Your phone died?! That's it?!

53:18.487 --> 53:20.031
I didn't mean to scare you, I swear.

53:20.114 --> 53:22.283
Come down here right now!

53:23.409 --> 53:25.328
-Be careful.
-Not you.

53:25.411 --> 53:27.121
You stay up there.

53:35.212 --> 53:37.131
Dad, I'm sorry, okay?

53:37.214 --> 53:38.382
You're sorry you got caught.

53:38.466 --> 53:40.468
No, I'm not. I'm sorry...

53:40.551 --> 53:42.345
I didn't mean to, like,
cause a whole thing.

53:42.428 --> 53:44.096
Did you give any thought
as to what would happen

53:44.180 --> 53:45.556
when I woke up and you weren't there?

53:45.640 --> 53:47.600
-I told you...
-I know you didn't.

53:47.683 --> 53:49.852
What happened to you being
a kid I could trust?

53:49.936 --> 53:50.937
I am. I am.

53:51.020 --> 53:53.147
-I-I just... I wasn't...

53:59.737 --> 54:01.781
What?

54:05.368 --> 54:06.702
I need you to drive.

54:06.786 --> 54:10.122
I'm, uh, I'm having
a vision thing right now.

54:30.851 --> 54:35.690
♪ For a second,
I forgot that I could have my way ♪

54:35.773 --> 54:38.234
♪ Enough of this, enough of that ♪

54:38.317 --> 54:40.444
♪ The idea is a slave ♪

54:40.528 --> 54:43.698
♪ To some unknown territory ♪

54:43.781 --> 54:46.200
♪ Buried in your brain... ♪

54:46.283 --> 54:47.910
- You got to cover the pad
when you type your PIN.

54:47.994 --> 54:49.996
-Otherwise, somebody will...
-Yep, got it.

54:59.922 --> 55:01.757
I didn't know your headaches
were this bad.

55:01.841 --> 55:03.843
You never tell me anything.

55:06.929 --> 55:10.933
♪ Enough of this-that,
this-that, this-that ♪

55:11.017 --> 55:12.810
♪ Oh... ♪

55:14.311 --> 55:17.940
- I wish you could've seen
what I saw last night.

55:18.024 --> 55:20.609
The whole sky was full of shooting stars.

55:22.319 --> 55:26.782
I know it sounds dumb,
but made me feel really small.

55:28.868 --> 55:32.997
One day, when me being an asshole
is behind us,

55:33.080 --> 55:35.666
we should go back to that field.

55:35.750 --> 55:37.877
Getting to see a meteor shower
in a place like that

55:37.960 --> 55:40.421
is something you should do before you die.

56:00.107 --> 56:02.818
-♪ I gotta leave my home ♪

56:02.902 --> 56:05.071
♪ Leave my soul and break away... ♪

56:05.154 --> 56:07.907
I guess I don't get
a fancy preprinted one.

56:07.990 --> 56:09.200
I should use a fake name.

56:09.283 --> 56:11.202
I would've made a great Ophelia.

56:11.285 --> 56:13.871
Use your real name.

56:13.954 --> 56:16.040
Hey, don't slouch. Stand up straight.

56:16.123 --> 56:19.043
What's with the posture police?

56:20.336 --> 56:23.923
I just... I want people's
first impressions of you to be good.

56:24.006 --> 56:25.758
What people?

56:25.841 --> 56:26.842
Hmm?

56:26.926 --> 56:28.219
Are you stress-sweating?

56:28.302 --> 56:30.137
Is this what a midlife crisis is?

56:30.221 --> 56:31.305
No.

56:31.388 --> 56:33.224
Yes.

56:33.307 --> 56:35.309
I just need a drink.

56:43.317 --> 56:45.486
The thing is...

56:46.946 --> 56:50.074
You said it was weird
that I wanted to come to this reunion.

56:50.157 --> 56:51.283
You were right.

56:51.367 --> 56:52.910
Obviously.

56:58.916 --> 57:01.377
It's just, um...

57:02.461 --> 57:04.255
-I wanted you to meet...
-- If you don't give me

57:04.338 --> 57:06.257
the biggest bear hug
of your life right now,

57:06.340 --> 57:08.634
I'm gonna cut off your arms
and wrap them around myself

57:08.717 --> 57:10.636
in a very sad and pathetic way.

57:10.719 --> 57:12.388
-Get over here.
-How the hell are you, Guy?

57:12.471 --> 57:14.306
Oh, forget me.

57:14.390 --> 57:15.599
Wally! Oh!

57:15.683 --> 57:16.892
I barely recognize you without those...

57:16.976 --> 57:19.728
Oh, God, please don't say bangs.

57:19.812 --> 57:21.355
-Cute Beetlejuice bangs.
-They were Dad's fault.

57:21.438 --> 57:23.357
But, you know,
they actually weren't as bad

57:23.440 --> 57:25.442
-as his frosted tips.
-Yeah, well, see,

57:25.526 --> 57:28.195
I'm still in therapy
for the year that my mother

57:28.279 --> 57:29.363
-let me grow a rat tail.

57:29.446 --> 57:31.532
Um, what's a rat tail again?

57:31.615 --> 57:33.951
God, we're so old.

57:34.994 --> 57:37.413
-Right?
-What?

57:37.496 --> 57:40.666
Wow, you used to wait a little longer
before tuning me out.

57:40.749 --> 57:42.334
-No, I'm sorry.

57:42.418 --> 57:43.460
It's a lot to take in.

57:43.544 --> 57:45.754
Right. Well, come and meet Samuel.

57:45.838 --> 57:48.340
I've definitely just left him alone
at a reunion

57:48.424 --> 57:50.176
where he knows absolutely no one.

57:50.259 --> 57:52.261
Join the club.

57:54.805 --> 57:56.432
This DJ is awful.

57:56.515 --> 57:59.143
When in the history of banquet halls
has a DJ ever been good?

57:59.226 --> 58:01.145
He doesn't have to be this bad.

58:01.228 --> 58:02.521
-- You're dancing?
-- Well, I'm-a always dance

58:02.605 --> 58:04.190
regardless of the quality of the music.

58:04.273 --> 58:06.108
I listen to my own playlist in my head.

58:06.192 --> 58:07.902
Mm.

58:07.985 --> 58:09.320
Park.

58:09.403 --> 58:11.697
Why aren't you up there
reliving your glory days?

58:11.780 --> 58:13.782
-What glory days?
-- Max used to be

58:13.866 --> 58:15.326
one of the broodiest singers
this side of the Mississippi.

58:15.409 --> 58:16.952
Aren't we on the Mississippi?

58:17.036 --> 58:19.371
We don't need to talk about this, okay?

58:19.455 --> 58:20.456
Yes, we do.

58:20.539 --> 58:23.751
I so wanted him to go pro
so I could make a career out of,

58:23.834 --> 58:25.878
-"Oh, no, I'm with the band, so..."

58:25.961 --> 58:28.005
-Were you really that good?
-- Oh, yes.

58:28.088 --> 58:29.965
I mean, girls in bars took their tops off.

58:30.049 --> 58:31.675
What?

58:31.759 --> 58:33.093
To be clear, it's New Orleans.

58:33.177 --> 58:35.512
Girls take their tops off
when a garbage truck goes by.

58:35.596 --> 58:38.432
-Uh, I'll be right back.
-Cool.

58:40.142 --> 58:41.810
We'll just stay here.

58:53.113 --> 58:54.365
Hi. This is Jane.

58:54.448 --> 58:56.700
-This is my wife Jane.
-Hi.

58:56.784 --> 58:58.661
H-Hold on.

58:58.744 --> 59:00.955
Excuse me.

59:01.038 --> 59:02.206
Max.

59:08.420 --> 59:09.588
Dale.

59:13.050 --> 59:15.469
Oh. Okay.

59:15.552 --> 59:17.638
-Great to see you, man.

59:17.721 --> 59:19.765
Yeah. Did you get my messages?

59:19.848 --> 59:21.684
No. Did you call me?

59:21.767 --> 59:23.727
Facebook. I don't have your phone number.

