probably since...

59:39.243 --> 59:41.578
Since Nicole left me.

59:42.621 --> 59:43.789
-Uh...
-Where is she?

59:43.872 --> 59:45.666
Is she here?

59:46.959 --> 59:49.169
Oh, wow, I-I just assumed you knew.

59:49.253 --> 59:51.171
Knew what?

59:51.255 --> 59:53.841
I'm here with, uh...

59:53.924 --> 59:56.218
wife two, uh, Jane.

59:57.594 --> 59:59.596
Let me buy you a drink.

1:00:01.181 --> 1:00:02.599
It's an open bar.

1:00:02.683 --> 1:00:03.726
Okay.

1:00:03.809 --> 1:00:05.686
Maybe I can...

1:00:05.769 --> 1:00:07.813
get you a free drink.

1:00:07.896 --> 1:00:09.982
-- He's cute. I get it.
-- Mm-hmm.

1:00:10.065 --> 1:00:12.359
I can see his confidence
even through the phone, child.

1:00:12.443 --> 1:00:14.570
So why would I try to kiss another guy?

1:00:14.653 --> 1:00:17.072
-Alcohol?

1:00:17.156 --> 1:00:19.325
Alcohol is always the answer
to that question.

1:00:19.408 --> 1:00:21.118
-Don't worry.

1:00:21.201 --> 1:00:23.579
Everyone always makes dumb decisions
when they're drunk.

1:00:23.662 --> 1:00:24.830
-I don't.
-I mean...

1:00:24.913 --> 1:00:26.749
-What? You don't?

1:00:28.167 --> 1:00:29.543
We met at a bar.

1:00:29.626 --> 1:00:30.919
Yeah, that was not a dumb decision.

1:00:31.003 --> 1:00:33.464
Who's that guy my dad's with?

1:00:33.547 --> 1:00:38.177
Uh... that would be Dale the douchebag.

1:00:38.260 --> 1:00:39.261
Huh.

1:00:42.056 --> 1:00:43.807
So what happened with Nicole?

1:00:44.808 --> 1:00:46.727
That's a really beautiful story.

1:00:46.810 --> 1:00:48.312
We got divorced.

1:00:48.395 --> 1:00:49.646
A few years ago now.

1:00:49.730 --> 1:00:51.148
Thought you were soul mates.

1:00:51.231 --> 1:00:54.610
We were soul mates for a little while.

1:00:55.903 --> 1:00:58.864
And then, uh, she left me, too.

1:00:58.947 --> 1:01:01.492
I, uh...

1:01:01.575 --> 1:01:03.285
I've thought about you, actually.

1:01:03.369 --> 1:01:05.537
And I, um...

1:01:06.705 --> 1:01:08.207
I really regret it.

1:01:08.290 --> 1:01:09.875
All of that.

1:01:10.959 --> 1:01:13.087
We're in the same boat, Max.

1:01:13.170 --> 1:01:16.173
And I know it's 15 years too late,
but I'm sorry.

1:01:17.341 --> 1:01:19.802
-Did you have kids?
-No. Ugh.

1:01:19.885 --> 1:01:22.096
Then our boats weren't even
in the same fucking marina.

1:01:22.179 --> 1:01:23.222
How is Wally?

1:01:23.305 --> 1:01:24.765
Don't do that. Don't do that.

1:01:24.848 --> 1:01:26.016
Okay.

1:01:26.100 --> 1:01:27.476
I was just trying to reconnect with you.

1:01:27.559 --> 1:01:30.145
All right, where's Nicole now?

1:01:30.229 --> 1:01:34.733
Uh, I pay alimony to someplace,
uh, near Tampa.

1:01:34.817 --> 1:01:36.318
♪ You got me feeling hella good ♪

1:01:36.402 --> 1:01:37.778
♪ So let's just keep on dancing... ♪

1:01:39.029 --> 1:01:41.031
I don't even recognize half these people.
Do you know these people?

1:01:41.115 --> 1:01:43.325
I need her address.

1:01:43.409 --> 1:01:44.952
-What for?
-I think you can do

1:01:45.035 --> 1:01:46.870
this one thing for me, okay?

1:01:46.954 --> 1:01:48.122
Pull up her address.

1:01:50.457 --> 1:01:52.251
This...

1:01:52.334 --> 1:01:54.420
better not be some kind
of revenge fantasy shit.

1:01:54.503 --> 1:01:55.921
Pull up the address.

1:01:56.004 --> 1:01:57.798
I'm doing that.

1:02:00.551 --> 1:02:02.261
You don't have a phone number.

1:02:02.344 --> 1:02:04.388
We only speak through lawyers now.

1:02:10.602 --> 1:02:11.854
So I guess we're good now.

1:02:11.937 --> 1:02:14.064
Oh, God, fuck off.

1:02:14.148 --> 1:02:16.984
Hey, Max,
I know you think of me as the bad guy,

1:02:17.067 --> 1:02:20.946
but it's not like
you were some innocent victim.

1:02:24.700 --> 1:02:26.410
♪ You got me feeling hella good ♪

1:02:26.493 --> 1:02:28.954
♪ So let's just keep on dancing... ♪

1:02:33.250 --> 1:02:35.085
Holy shit.

1:02:35.169 --> 1:02:37.337
♪ So I'm gonna keep on dancing ♪

1:02:37.421 --> 1:02:39.756
♪ Dancing. ♪

1:02:53.812 --> 1:02:56.523
I've never seen Dad like that before.

1:02:56.607 --> 1:02:58.025
Oh, he can take a punch.

1:02:58.108 --> 1:03:00.110
The man once got an ass tattoo in Vegas.

1:03:00.194 --> 1:03:01.487
Are you really surprised?

1:03:01.570 --> 1:03:03.947
-Wait. Snake eyes?
-- You never know

1:03:04.031 --> 1:03:06.408
when to stop talking.

1:03:06.492 --> 1:03:08.118
You didn't hear that from me.

1:03:09.161 --> 1:03:12.372
When did he get so boring?

1:03:12.456 --> 1:03:13.874
He grew up.

1:03:26.136 --> 1:03:29.765
♪ Take it slow ♪

1:03:29.848 --> 1:03:35.604
♪ I take it slow riding the backroads... ♪

1:03:35.687 --> 1:03:38.273
So...

1:03:38.357 --> 1:03:40.567
he's the one she left us for?

1:03:41.777 --> 1:03:44.112
Why didn't you ever tell me
he was your best friend?

1:03:44.196 --> 1:03:45.906
I wouldn't call him my best friend.

1:03:45.989 --> 1:03:48.575
And-and why didn't you tell me
we were coming to see her?

1:03:50.869 --> 1:03:52.955
I didn't know what she'd be like.

1:03:53.038 --> 1:03:56.833
But I guess we're both gonna find out
if we're heading to Florida.

1:03:57.876 --> 1:03:59.753
Does she want to meet me?

1:04:02.506 --> 1:04:04.007
How could she not?

1:04:04.091 --> 1:04:06.677
That's not an answer.

1:04:06.760 --> 1:04:08.554
Do you want to meet her?

1:04:08.637 --> 1:04:12.599
I've stalked every Nicole Burke
I could find online.

1:04:12.683 --> 1:04:14.309
You have?

1:04:14.393 --> 1:04:16.395
They're mostly white ladies.

1:04:17.312 --> 1:04:21.733
She's going by her stage name:
Nicole Genevieve.

1:04:22.734 --> 1:04:24.111
She's an actress?

1:04:24.194 --> 1:04:25.654
She was gonna be.

1:04:25.737 --> 1:04:29.950
She said L.A. was, uh, too hard.

1:04:30.033 --> 1:04:31.618
That's what took her to New York.

1:04:31.702 --> 1:04:33.662
That and Dale.

1:04:33.745 --> 1:04:35.289
Don't hold Dale against her, okay?

1:04:35.372 --> 1:04:37.207
Her leaving was...

1:04:37.291 --> 1:04:39.126
my fault.

1:04:40.669 --> 1:04:42.129
Wait. What?

1:04:42.212 --> 1:04:43.338
What do you mean?

1:04:43.422 --> 1:04:45.340
Not... not entirely.

1:04:45.424 --> 1:04:47.759
It is complicated.

1:04:47.843 --> 1:04:49.052
What's complicated?

1:04:49.136 --> 1:04:51.054
You-you forced her
to hook up with another guy?

1:04:51.138 --> 1:04:52.472
No, um...

1:04:52.556 --> 1:04:54.266
Dad, she's the one who cheated.

1:05:02.983 --> 1:05:04.192
What?

1:05:07.529 --> 1:05:09.156
I cheated first.

1:05:13.035 --> 1:05:14.244
Sweetheart...

1:05:30.010 --> 1:05:31.720
Hey, gumbo's here.

1:05:34.431 --> 1:05:35.557
Come on.

1:05:35.641 --> 1:05:37.184
It's been a long day.

1:05:40.771 --> 1:05:42.272
So?

1:05:42.356 --> 1:05:44.232
What?

1:05:44.316 --> 1:05:46.652
Why'd you do it?

1:05:46.735 --> 1:05:49.946
And I don't want some bullshit answer.

1:05:50.030 --> 1:05:52.741
I don't have a reason
that's gonna make it better.

1:05:55.243 --> 1:05:56.870
We had a fight.

1:05:58.830 --> 1:06:00.832
We had a lot of fights.

1:06:03.835 --> 1:06:06.838
I went out and...

1:06:06.922 --> 1:06:08.882
I got drunk.

1:06:10.217 --> 1:06:11.426
And that was that.

1:06:15.722 --> 1:06:17.808
Just once?

1:06:22.771 --> 1:06:24.439
I'm sorry.

1:06:26.942 --> 1:06:30.237
♪ Matching socks and old cartoons ♪

1:06:32.322 --> 1:06:35.409
♪ Wish those days never changed. ♪

1:07:24.624 --> 1:07:25.959
-Hello.
-- Hey.

1:07:26.042 --> 1:07:28.044
It's early.
I figured I'd get your voice mail.

1:07:28.128 --> 1:07:30.088
Mm, yeah. Summer school grades are due,

1:07:30.172 --> 1:07:34.009
and I put off submitting them
until an hour before the deadline.

1:07:34.092 --> 1:07:35.510
Very responsible.

1:07:35.594 --> 1:07:37.179
I thought so.

1:07:38.638 --> 1:07:40.640
How are you? Sorry.

1:07:40.724 --> 1:07:44.436
I know that's-that's
the world's dumbest question.

1:07:44.519 --> 1:07:46.772
I just mean...

1:07:47.939 --> 1:07:51.193
...you know, the...
on the brain tumor front.

1:07:51.276 --> 1:07:52.778
It's actually a bone tumor.

1:07:52.861 --> 1:07:54.780
Um, near my brain.

1:07:54.863 --> 1:07:56.990
Wh-- Is that better?

1:07:57.073 --> 1:07:58.867
No.

1:08:00.660 --> 1:08:02.329
Are you okay?

1:08:04.873 --> 1:08:07.125
I'm the same, I guess.

1:08:07.209 --> 1:08:08.418
Well, that's good.

1:08:08.502 --> 1:08:11.254
Uh, I mean, not good, but...

1:08:11.338 --> 1:08:13.340
but good that you're not worse.

1:08:15.217 --> 1:08:16.635
Yeah.

1:08:16.718 --> 1:08:19.262
It's good that I'm not worse.

1:08:26.144 --> 1:08:28.021
You ready to hit the road?

1:08:28.104 --> 1:08:30.148
Yeah, but I'm starving.

1:08:30.232 --> 1:08:32.108
Barely ate anything last night.

1:08:32.192 --> 1:08:34.319
'Cause I was mad at you.

1:08:35.821 --> 1:08:37.489
Are you still?

1:08:38.615 --> 1:08:41.117
Are you gonna hide more shit from me?

1:08:46.248 --> 1:08:48.208
No.

1:08:51.336 --> 1:08:52.754
Then no.

1:08:52.838 --> 1:08:54.464
I'm not mad at you.

1:09:00.887 --> 1:09:02.597
Look, um...

1:09:04.558 --> 1:09:08.562
...whatever else happened
between you guys...

1:09:11.189 --> 1:09:13.316
...you're the one that stayed with me.

1:09:28.915 --> 1:09:31.209
-Okay.

1:09:41.803 --> 1:09:45.807
♪ Sure, we sometimes wonder why... ♪

1:09:47.017 --> 1:09:48.810
Last night, Guy kept talking about

1:09:48.894 --> 1:09:50.604
how he thought you were gonna end
up a rock star.

1:09:50.687 --> 1:09:52.814
I've never even heard you sing.

1:09:52.898 --> 1:09:54.399
What are you talking about?
Of course you have.

1:09:54.482 --> 1:09:56.610
I don't mean to the radio
or when you used to sing

1:09:56.693 --> 1:10:00.113
"My Wally Lies Over the Ocean"
to put me to sleep.

1:10:00.196 --> 1:10:01.740
I told you I used to play guitar.

1:10:01.823 --> 1:10:02.866
And some drums.

1:10:02.949 --> 1:10:04.659
Yeah, but I assumed you meant, like,

1:10:04.743 --> 1:10:06.995
you took lessons or something
since you don't own a guitar.

1:10:07.078 --> 1:10:09.164
Sold it.

1:10:09.247 --> 1:10:11.166
That's sad, Dad.

1:10:11.249 --> 1:10:14.920
For a while, I was...

1:10:15.003 --> 1:10:17.047
really serious about music.

1:10:18.715 --> 1:10:20.800
I thought I could make a living off of it.

1:10:21.801 --> 1:10:23.887
Until one day, you woke up thinking,

1:10:23.970 --> 1:10:27.182
"My life would be so much better
if I got a job where I wore loafers."

1:10:27.265 --> 1:10:28.850
I do not wear loafers.

1:10:28.934 --> 1:10:31.227
Mm. What are those?

1:10:31.311 --> 1:10:32.771
These have laces.

1:10:32.854 --> 1:10:34.230
Oh.

1:10:34.314 --> 1:10:36.816
Loafers don't have laces.
That's what makes them loafers.

1:10:38.735 --> 1:10:41.529
Look, 99% of people who want
to make a living doing music or art

1:10:41.613 --> 1:10:43.949
are never gonna be successful,
and that's just facts.

1:10:44.032 --> 1:10:45.241
So you just gave it up?

1:10:45.325 --> 1:10:47.243
I could've struggled for years,

1:10:47.327 --> 1:10:49.537
could've given up everything
and still never made it.

1:10:49.621 --> 1:10:51.748
Or we could be rich and famous right now.

1:10:51.831 --> 1:10:53.708
Sorry to disappoint.

1:10:53.792 --> 1:10:56.169
Were you really that good?

1:10:59.214 --> 1:11:00.632
I thought I was.

1:11:02.008 --> 1:11:04.010
Did she think you were good?

1:11:05.595 --> 1:11:08.014
It's probably what made her
fall in love with me.

1:11:14.104 --> 1:11:17.899
I wish I knew when we started this trip
I was gonna meet my mom.

1:11:20.777 --> 1:11:24.364
I probably would've packed nicer clothes.

1:11:25.699 --> 1:11:27.826
Just...

1:11:27.909 --> 1:11:30.120
I want her to like me.

1:11:36.501 --> 1:11:38.461
- I thought you were going
with the orange dress.

1:11:38.545 --> 1:11:40.171
The orange dress looked great.

1:11:40.255 --> 1:11:42.674
I'm just trying on one more.

1:11:42.757 --> 1:11:45.802
What do you think of this one?

1:11:49.973 --> 1:11:51.683
You look, uh...

1:11:53.685 --> 1:11:55.979
It's not like
it's my wedding dress or something.

1:11:57.230 --> 1:11:58.523
I know. I just...

1:11:58.606 --> 1:12:00.900
Okay, so this one or the orange one?

1:12:01.943 --> 1:12:04.195
Both.

1:12:04.279 --> 1:12:06.281
It's $110.

1:12:16.624 --> 1:12:18.334
Explain to me why we're here.

1:12:18.418 --> 1:12:21.713
- Because every father
should teach his daughter how to dance

1:12:21.796 --> 1:12:24.049
before her wedding day.

1:12:24.132 --> 1:12:25.633
Don't you think?

1:12:25.717 --> 1:12:29.929
Yeah, I'm pretty sure we got tons of time
before you need to worry about that.

1:12:37.771 --> 1:12:39.522
Is this about her?

1:12:39.606 --> 1:12:43.068
Because it's not like I'm gonna pick her
over you or something.

1:12:48.490 --> 1:12:50.450
Let's dance, Wallis.

1:12:51.618 --> 1:12:53.620
♪ ♪

1:12:58.374 --> 1:13:00.960
I don't know what I'm doing.

1:13:01.044 --> 1:13:02.462
It's okay.

1:13:02.545 --> 1:13:06.758
Can I just stand on your feet
like I did when I was a little kid?

1:13:06.841 --> 1:13:08.468
You actually never did that.

1:13:08.551 --> 1:13:09.969
You always chose to be difficult.

1:13:10.053 --> 1:13:12.639
That doesn't sound like me at all.

1:13:12.722 --> 1:13:13.848
Oh, doesn't it?

1:13:13.932 --> 1:13:15.934
Doesn't sound like you?

1:13:18.144 --> 1:13:19.729
Come here.

1:13:19.813 --> 1:13:21.314
Trust yourself.

1:13:26.152 --> 1:13:29.155
You're gonna meet a lot of guys
in your life, Wally.

1:13:30.782 --> 1:13:32.909
You're gonna like some.

1:13:32.992 --> 1:13:35.328
Gonna hate a few.

1:13:35.411 --> 1:13:37.413
You might love a few.

1:13:38.748 --> 1:13:42.460
But I don't want you to marry someone
unless he is a good man.

1:13:44.504 --> 1:13:46.339
Okay.

1:13:47.382 --> 1:13:48.967
Uh, it's just...

1:13:50.426 --> 1:13:51.886
You are becoming a woman.

1:13:57.350 --> 1:13:59.519
You have a fire inside you, Wally.

1:14:01.146 --> 1:14:05.191
Life is gonna pull some pretty
shitty moves to try and put it out.

1:14:07.235 --> 1:14:11.990
And when it happens, I just want the guy
next to you helping you light it again.

1:14:12.073 --> 1:14:13.491
Okay?

1:14:18.788 --> 1:14:20.415
How will I know?

1:14:20.498 --> 1:14:23.751
Well, for one,

1:14:23.835 --> 1:14:26.504
good man will take you dancing
if you want him to.

1:14:29.674 --> 1:14:33.678
Doesn't have to be as skilled
as your old man, but...

1:14:33.761 --> 1:14:36.848
he should jump at the opportunity.

1:14:36.931 --> 1:14:39.184
'Cause he'll want to make you happy.

1:14:43.062 --> 1:14:45.523
A good man will take me dancing.

1:14:45.607 --> 1:14:47.317
You got it.

1:14:53.364 --> 1:14:55.366
♪ ♪

1:15:29.400 --> 1:15:30.526
What's up?

1:15:30.610 --> 1:15:32.612
Hey, Glenn.

1:15:32.695 --> 1:15:35.156
Uh, there's something important
I need to tell you.

1:15:35.240 --> 1:15:36.574
'Kay.

1:15:36.658 --> 1:15:38.534
Next time you decide you want to see me

1:15:38.618 --> 1:15:41.037
when you get bored
of everyone else, don't.

1:15:41.120 --> 1:15:45.750
Maybe you just have really nice hair
or really good pheromones or something.

1:15:45.833 --> 1:15:47.669
I don't know, but...

1:15:49.003 --> 1:15:51.798
I guess what I'm trying to say
is I've realized

1:15:51.881 --> 1:15:54.801
that you don't actually make me feel good.

1:15:54.884 --> 1:15:55.885
Wait.

1:15:55.969 --> 1:15:58.346
Have a good night, babe.

1:16:03.351 --> 1:16:04.936
K.O.

1:16:07.855 --> 1:16:09.357
Loser.

1:16:39.429 --> 1:16:41.306
You sure this is her place?

1:16:41.389 --> 1:16:43.766
Six one eight.

1:16:43.850 --> 1:16:46.436
That is definitely it.

1:16:49.981 --> 1:16:51.649
Whenever you're ready.

1:16:54.569 --> 1:16:56.029
I can't do this.

1:16:56.112 --> 1:16:57.864
What do you mean?

1:16:57.947 --> 1:16:59.282
You're a doer. You face things.

1:16:59.365 --> 1:17:01.242
I've always admired that about you.

1:17:01.326 --> 1:17:03.786
Dad, we can't just be like, "Hi, ex-wife.

1:17:03.870 --> 1:17:05.705
"Look who's here,
the baby you left behind.

1:17:05.788 --> 1:17:07.457
Like her dress?"

1:17:07.540 --> 1:17:09.959
We can't show up unannounced, okay?

1:17:10.043 --> 1:17:12.462
You just-- you go first and prep her.

1:17:12.545 --> 1:17:14.797
-Listen, I think...
-No, Dad, please.

1:17:14.881 --> 1:17:16.507
I shouldn't surprise her.

1:17:19.552 --> 1:17:21.179
'Kay.

1:17:27.018 --> 1:17:28.770
Try to keep from, uh--

1:17:28.853 --> 1:17:32.231
what'd you call it?--
stress-sweating while you wait.

1:17:53.544 --> 1:17:55.213
Max.

1:17:55.296 --> 1:17:56.839
Hi.

1:17:59.092 --> 1:18:00.968
What are you doing here?

1:18:01.052 --> 1:18:03.471
I was in the neighborhood.

1:18:03.554 --> 1:18:06.516
My neighborhood?

1:18:06.599 --> 1:18:08.518
How'd you find me?

1:18:08.601 --> 1:18:10.895
I ran into your ex-husband.

1:18:10.978 --> 1:18:13.398
Your other ex-husband.

1:18:13.481 --> 1:18:15.024
Listen, I'm sorry.

1:18:15.108 --> 1:18:19.904
I would've called, but, um,
you are, uh, really hard to find.

1:18:19.987 --> 1:18:23.908
I mean, seriously, witness protection
could use some tips from you.

1:18:30.206 --> 1:18:32.667
Can I come in?

1:18:32.750 --> 1:18:35.336
Uh, the house is a mess.

1:18:35.420 --> 1:18:37.463
Let's go around back.

1:18:37.547 --> 1:18:39.298
Okay.

1:18:39.382 --> 1:18:41.801
Yeah. Yeah.

1:18:54.939 --> 1:18:56.441
Shit.

1:19:01.070 --> 1:19:04.157
She just wants to meet her mom.

1:19:04.240 --> 1:19:06.951
According to the courts,
I'm not really fit to be her mom.

1:19:07.034 --> 1:19:08.536
Hey, please, don't take that out on her.

1:19:08.619 --> 1:19:10.997
You left. What was I supposed to do?

1:19:11.080 --> 1:19:13.124
Do you know how hard it is
to lose the rights to your kid?

1:19:13.207 --> 1:19:15.501
I don't want to rehash everything
right now, okay?

1:19:19.881 --> 1:19:21.299
Okay.

1:19:21.382 --> 1:19:25.803
So when'd you end up in, uh... Florida?

1:19:25.887 --> 1:19:27.597
Year and a half ago.

1:19:27.680 --> 1:19:30.308
It's a long story, but...

1:19:30.391 --> 1:19:33.644
I met Tom, and he helped me
to get my life together.

1:19:33.728 --> 1:19:35.521
Tom.

1:19:35.605 --> 1:19:36.689
Yeah.

1:19:36.772 --> 1:19:38.483
Mm-hmm.

1:19:40.151 --> 1:19:42.612
Is he why you don't want to meet her?

1:19:42.695 --> 1:19:45.948
Of course I want to meet her.
I think about her a lot.

1:19:47.575 --> 1:19:49.577
But...

1:19:49.660 --> 1:19:51.579
things are too complicated right now.

1:19:52.622 --> 1:19:54.290
What do you want me to tell her?

1:19:57.293 --> 1:19:59.629
-You should go.
-Well, you got to answer me.

1:19:59.712 --> 1:20:01.506
-What do I tell her? What do I tell her?
-I don't know.

1:20:01.589 --> 1:20:03.299
I don't know!

1:20:03.382 --> 1:20:05.384
You can't just show up out of nowhere.
That's on you.

1:20:05.468 --> 1:20:06.844
Oh, come on.

1:20:06.928 --> 1:20:10.389
It's just not a good time in my life.

1:20:11.724 --> 1:20:13.893
But maybe we can meet one day.

1:20:13.976 --> 1:20:16.479
You really hate your brief stint
at motherhood that much?

1:20:16.562 --> 1:20:18.064
-Stop.
-Or do you hate me so much

1:20:18.147 --> 1:20:19.440
that you're willing to hurt your daughter?

1:20:19.524 --> 1:20:22.610
She is waiting in the car!

1:20:22.693 --> 1:20:24.862
I'm sorry I'm not who you want me to be.

1:20:24.946 --> 1:20:26.489
That makes two of us.

1:20:26.572 --> 1:20:28.908
I don't have time for you
to figure your shit out.

1:20:28.991 --> 1:20:30.326
What does that mean?

1:20:31.911 --> 1:20:34.205
You're her only family.

1:20:34.288 --> 1:20:35.540
Other than me.

1:20:43.506 --> 1:20:44.674
Yours?

1:20:46.759 --> 1:20:48.219
Elizabeth.

1:20:49.470 --> 1:20:51.389
She'll be one next month.

1:20:54.767 --> 1:20:57.019
I'm sorry, Max.

1:20:57.103 --> 1:20:58.729
I am.

1:21:01.315 --> 1:21:02.400
-Nicole, come on.
-No.

1:21:02.483 --> 1:21:04.151
You can't just...

1:21:04.235 --> 1:21:06.362
You have to go.

1:21:28.134 --> 1:21:30.011
Hey. Wh-What-what did you say?

1:21:30.094 --> 1:21:31.596
What did she say? Are we going in?

1:21:31.679 --> 1:21:34.140
Little glitch in the plan, hon.

1:21:34.223 --> 1:21:36.517
She doesn't want to meet me.

1:21:36.601 --> 1:21:38.477
Course she does. It's, um...

1:21:38.561 --> 1:21:40.980
We had to go around back
because she's having her floors redone

1:21:41.063 --> 1:21:44.150
and the house is full of workers,
but we're coming back tomorrow.

1:21:45.276 --> 1:21:47.278
-Really?
-Yeah.

1:21:48.362 --> 1:21:49.614
Let's go somewhere.

1:21:49.697 --> 1:21:51.782
Take our minds off this
for a little bit, okay?

1:22:00.750 --> 1:22:02.668
Come on, what happened in there?

1:22:02.752 --> 1:22:04.503
-- Told you what happened.
-No, you-you gave me

1:22:04.587 --> 1:22:07.548
the Great Illustrated Classics
abridged version.

1:22:07.632 --> 1:22:08.633
I-I want the play-by-play.

1:22:08.716 --> 1:22:11.135
So, you're at the door, ding-dong. Then?

1:22:12.345 --> 1:22:13.721
We talked for a little bit.

1:22:13.804 --> 1:22:15.848
-She a crackhead or something?
-What?

1:22:15.931 --> 1:22:18.100
No. What kind of a question is that?

1:22:18.184 --> 1:22:21.145
You've never been more evasive
in my entire life, not even when I was six

1:22:21.228 --> 1:22:23.564
and we were watching  Friends
and I asked you what sex was.

1:22:23.648 --> 1:22:25.107
I don't know what you want me to tell you.

1:22:25.191 --> 1:22:26.442
We talked for a little bit.

1:22:26.525 --> 1:22:27.610
She had people over.

1:22:27.693 --> 1:22:29.236
She couldn't focus on everything at once.

1:22:29.320 --> 1:22:31.238
-That's all.
-Why are you lying to me?

1:22:31.322 --> 1:22:32.490
I'm not.

1:22:32.573 --> 1:22:34.158
There wasn't a work van
on the street, Dad.

1:22:34.241 --> 1:22:35.409
There weren't any cars.

1:22:35.493 --> 1:22:36.535
She didn't have workers there.

1:22:36.619 --> 1:22:38.996
She's not getting her floors redone.

1:22:39.080 --> 1:22:41.040
Okay? So, ei-either she's a crackhead

1:22:41.123 --> 1:22:43.084
and-and you just didn't want me
to meet her

1:22:43.167 --> 1:22:45.169
or she doesn't want to meet me.

1:22:49.131 --> 1:22:50.800
She has a baby.

1:22:52.677 --> 1:22:56.305
She said her life is too complicated
to meet you right now. Come here.

1:22:56.389 --> 1:22:57.932
Stop. Stop telling me things
are complicated.

1:22:58.015 --> 1:22:59.433
It means nothing.

1:22:59.517 --> 1:23:00.768
Wally, we got to talk about this.

1:23:00.851 --> 1:23:02.311
What is wrong with you?!

1:23:02.395 --> 1:23:03.604
You brought us to a freaking nude beach?!

1:23:03.688 --> 1:23:05.856
- I didn't know it was a nude beach.
I just GPS'd the closest one.

1:23:05.940 --> 1:23:07.858
'Cause I needed to be further scarred
by this day.

1:23:07.942 --> 1:23:09.235
You can never tell anyone
that I brought you here, okay?

1:23:09.318 --> 1:23:11.070
I would die
before I tell anyone about this!

1:23:13.489 --> 1:23:15.408
Dad, stop!

1:23:15.491 --> 1:23:16.659
Stop touching me!

1:23:16.742 --> 1:23:18.035
Wally, calm down! Calm down!

1:23:18.119 --> 1:23:19.995
No, I-I don't want to calm down!

1:23:20.079 --> 1:23:22.998
Did you think I wouldn't figure out
that she didn't want to meet me?

1:23:23.082 --> 1:23:24.667
Or w-were you gonna lie to me
again tomorrow

1:23:24.750 --> 1:23:26.752
and the next day and the next day?

1:23:26.836 --> 1:23:28.462
Clearly I didn't have a plan, okay?

1:23:28.546 --> 1:23:30.214
I just didn't want to see you sad.

1:23:30.297 --> 1:23:33.175
You know what?
That worked out perfect, Dad.

1:23:35.970 --> 1:23:38.180
What's her replacement kid's name?

1:23:38.264 --> 1:23:39.473
She's not a replacement.

1:23:39.557 --> 1:23:41.559
Maybe you don't know
the meaning of the word.

1:23:43.978 --> 1:23:46.021
Elizabeth.

1:23:47.064 --> 1:23:48.691
Dumbest name ever.

1:23:48.774 --> 1:23:51.277
She was just overwhelmed.

1:23:51.360 --> 1:23:53.320
Sweetheart, I know she'll come around.

1:23:55.448 --> 1:23:56.449
Wally.

1:23:57.825 --> 1:23:59.785
Wally. Wally?

1:23:59.869 --> 1:24:01.871
♪ ♪

1:24:28.981 --> 1:24:31.108
Wally? Can I come in?

1:24:33.027 --> 1:24:35.279
-Hey, Wall...

1:24:36.489 --> 1:24:37.823
-I'm ready to go home now.

1:24:37.907 --> 1:24:40.951
Hey. We're not leaving. Come on.

1:24:41.035 --> 1:24:42.578
I'm not gonna stay somewhere
where there's nothing for me.

1:24:42.661 --> 1:24:43.913
Listen, I'm not gonna drag you.

1:24:43.996 --> 1:24:46.040
You've dragged me this whole time!

1:24:46.123 --> 1:24:47.124
Wally!

1:24:47.208 --> 1:24:48.417
We're going home!

1:24:48.501 --> 1:24:51.003
No, we're not leaving until you meet her!

1:24:51.086 --> 1:24:53.088
I know deep down she wants to see you.

1:24:53.172 --> 1:24:54.548
Then why didn't she ever try to?

1:24:54.632 --> 1:24:56.926
God, I wish you never put this stupid idea
in my head!

1:24:57.009 --> 1:24:59.553
You should've just let me keep
this fantasy version of her

1:24:59.637 --> 1:25:02.890
that somewhere out there
was a woman who regretted abandoning me

1:25:02.973 --> 1:25:04.683
and wished she could have me back.

1:25:04.767 --> 1:25:06.227
But you didn't.

1:25:06.310 --> 1:25:07.436
You ruined everything.

1:25:07.520 --> 1:25:08.771
I want to go home.

1:25:10.231 --> 1:25:12.316
-You have to meet her.
-I thought I wasn't

1:25:12.399 --> 1:25:14.735
supposed to want someone
who doesn't want me back.

1:25:14.819 --> 1:25:16.445
So this is, this is different. Uh...

1:25:16.529 --> 1:25:17.947
Are you still in love with her?

1:25:21.659 --> 1:25:23.077
Not even close.

1:25:23.160 --> 1:25:25.454
So why are you doing this to me?

1:25:40.177 --> 1:25:41.720
Um...

1:25:51.605 --> 1:25:53.941
I have a tumor

1:25:54.024 --> 1:25:56.610
in my head

1:25:56.694 --> 1:26:00.030
that's giving me less than a year.

1:26:02.449 --> 1:26:08.205
If I let them operate to try to remove it,

1:26:08.289 --> 1:26:10.791
uh, they could kill me on the table.

1:26:12.042 --> 1:26:13.627
So I-I can't do that.

1:26:15.170 --> 1:26:19.425
I have to spend this year
fixing things for you while I still can.

1:26:20.759 --> 1:26:22.511
-Wally.

1:26:22.595 --> 1:26:25.431
-Wally. Wally.

1:26:25.514 --> 1:26:27.057
Wally?!

1:26:28.976 --> 1:26:31.186
Wally. Come on.

1:26:35.941 --> 1:26:37.651
-Wally?

1:26:37.735 --> 1:26:40.362
-Is everything okay?
-Yes, yes, everything is fine.

1:26:41.655 --> 1:26:43.490
-Hey!

1:26:43.574 --> 1:26:45.034
Turn the car off!

1:26:45.117 --> 1:26:46.118
-Turn the car off!

1:26:46.201 --> 1:26:47.453
No! Move!

1:26:54.251 --> 1:26:55.544
Hey, come on.

1:26:55.628 --> 1:26:57.421
Wally, let's talk about this.

1:27:00.424 --> 1:27:02.343
I know this sucks.

1:27:02.426 --> 1:27:04.511
-I get it, okay?
-Oh, you get it?

1:27:04.595 --> 1:27:06.555
-Whoa! Whoa! Slow down!

1:27:06.639 --> 1:27:08.223
-Put your belt on!

1:27:08.307 --> 1:27:10.351
-Ugh, get off! Stop!
-Put your belt on!

1:27:10.434 --> 1:27:12.102
-Slow down. Shit.

1:27:13.646 --> 1:27:16.023
Listen, I understand you're upset, okay?

1:27:16.106 --> 1:27:17.316
I'm obviously upset, too.

1:27:17.399 --> 1:27:18.692
-We need to talk about it.
-Oh, you don't want

1:27:18.776 --> 1:27:20.402
to congratulate me on my perfect merge?

1:27:20.486 --> 1:27:21.779
No! I want you to stop driving!

1:27:21.862 --> 1:27:23.030
I didn't make you come with me!

1:27:23.113 --> 1:27:24.990
-You are welcome to get out!

1:27:26.742 --> 1:27:28.827
This car can't handle any faster!

1:27:28.911 --> 1:27:30.829
Maybe you shouldn't have
an elderly car, then.

1:27:32.373 --> 1:27:33.916
Okay.

1:27:33.999 --> 1:27:35.876
All right, we're gonna get arrested.

1:27:35.960 --> 1:27:37.670
That's good. That's what I need right now.

1:27:41.423 --> 1:27:43.634
How many times
do I have to tell you to stop?!

1:27:43.717 --> 1:27:45.678
I don't know. I guess we'll see.

1:27:45.761 --> 1:27:47.596
What point is this proving?!

1:27:49.014 --> 1:27:50.516
Jesus!

1:27:50.599 --> 1:27:52.101
Wally! Stop!

1:27:55.312 --> 1:27:56.855
You could've killed somebody!

1:27:59.066 --> 1:28:01.527
-- You all right?
-Wally?

1:28:01.610 --> 1:28:03.028
Hey, where-where's she going?

1:28:03.112 --> 1:28:04.655
Wally!

1:28:06.240 --> 1:28:08.701
I'm sorry. I-I'll be right back!

1:28:08.784 --> 1:28:10.911
Sorry!

1:28:10.995 --> 1:28:12.538
Wally!

1:28:12.621 --> 1:28:15.082
Stop! Stop!

1:28:15.165 --> 1:28:16.500
Hey!

1:28:17.626 --> 1:28:19.461
Hey!

1:28:19.545 --> 1:28:21.630
Hey. What the hell was that?!

1:28:21.714 --> 1:28:24.383
-I hate you. I hate you.
-For what?

1:28:24.466 --> 1:28:26.844
You find out that you're...

1:28:26.927 --> 1:28:28.929
that you have a tumor,
and instead of telling me,

1:28:29.013 --> 1:28:31.682
you try to pawn me off onto some woman
who doesn't even want me?

1:28:31.765 --> 1:28:33.642
Do you not realize
how screwed-up that is?!

1:28:33.726 --> 1:28:36.603
Oh, fuck, Wally.

1:28:36.687 --> 1:28:38.564
When are you gonna grow up?!

1:28:38.647 --> 1:28:40.899
I am sorry that I am dying

1:28:40.983 --> 1:28:43.277
and something in this world
isn't about you.

1:28:43.360 --> 1:28:45.654
And I'm sorry that I gave up
on all the things

1:28:45.738 --> 1:28:47.656
that I wanted in life to make you happy.

1:28:47.740 --> 1:28:49.116
'Cause you know what?

1:28:49.199 --> 1:28:51.035
You are never happy!

1:28:51.118 --> 1:28:52.745
I didn't make you give up anything.

1:28:52.828 --> 1:28:55.247
That is all you
because that is what you do.

1:28:55.330 --> 1:28:58.250
You don't bet on yourself.
You don't believe you can win.

1:28:58.333 --> 1:29:01.670
But, hey, at least you're gonna leave me
with a clear philosophy, right?

1:29:01.754 --> 1:29:03.213
I'm not leaving you with that.

1:29:03.297 --> 1:29:06.592
Then why wouldn't you let them
try to take the tumor out?!

1:29:09.428 --> 1:29:11.555
What do you want me to say?

1:29:11.638 --> 1:29:14.725
That you're not gonna die.

1:29:14.808 --> 1:29:17.728
I thought you didn't want me
to lie to you, baby.

1:29:17.811 --> 1:29:21.607
Is it 100% certain
that the surgery won't work?

1:29:23.817 --> 1:29:25.694
-No, but...
-So, if you do nothing,

1:29:25.778 --> 1:29:30.324
you definitely die, and if you
do something, you potentially live.

1:29:30.407 --> 1:29:32.576
How is that not a clear choice?

1:29:35.871 --> 1:29:38.415
I don't want you for one year, Dad.

1:29:40.375 --> 1:29:42.920
I want you for my whole life.

1:29:43.962 --> 1:29:48.425
Don't you want to yell at me when I get
some stupid tattoo like you did?

1:29:48.509 --> 1:29:50.552
You're supposed to-- I don't know.

1:29:50.636 --> 1:29:53.305
You're supposed to laugh
when I trip at my own wedding.

1:29:53.388 --> 1:29:55.224
And I'm supposed to be obnoxious

1:29:55.307 --> 1:29:58.685
when you finally introduce me
to some woman you're dating.

1:29:58.769 --> 1:30:00.437
Dad, I love you.

1:30:00.521 --> 1:30:03.816
And I know I don't always show it,
and I'm sorry,

1:30:03.899 --> 1:30:06.860
but, uh, I thought we had more time.

1:30:06.944 --> 1:30:09.905
I thought we were gonna go back
to that field in Texas

1:30:09.988 --> 1:30:11.281
and watch the meteor shower.

1:30:11.365 --> 1:30:15.160
I thought... I thought we were gonna
do all that stuff together.

1:30:16.829 --> 1:30:18.497
Don't you want to?

1:30:21.500 --> 1:30:23.502
You have no idea.

1:30:24.586 --> 1:30:27.506
We don't get to unless you're willing
to take a chance.

1:30:29.174 --> 1:30:30.926
Please, Dad.

1:30:31.009 --> 1:30:32.928
I'd bet on you.

1:30:40.435 --> 1:30:41.895
Okay.

1:30:44.982 --> 1:30:46.275
Okay?

1:30:46.358 --> 1:30:47.901
-Okay.
-Okay?

1:30:47.985 --> 1:30:48.986
Okay.

1:31:04.042 --> 1:31:05.627
We were just standing still
and the girl...

1:31:07.254 --> 1:31:09.464
Am I grounded?

1:31:15.012 --> 1:31:16.388
One, two, three, huh!

1:31:16.471 --> 1:31:19.224
♪ Tommy used to work on the docks ♪

1:31:20.726 --> 1:31:23.687
♪ Union's been on strike,
he's down on his luck ♪

1:31:23.770 --> 1:31:26.523
♪ It's tough ♪

1:31:32.196 --> 1:31:36.116
♪ Gina works the diner all day ♪

1:31:36.200 --> 1:31:38.994
♪ Working for her man, she brings home ♪

1:31:42.289 --> 1:31:45.000
♪ Oh, for love ♪

1:31:45.083 --> 1:31:47.127
-♪ This one says ♪

1:31:47.211 --> 1:31:51.548
♪ "We gotta hold on
to what we've got, huh ♪

1:31:51.632 --> 1:31:55.469
♪ "Doesn't make a difference
if we make it or not, yeah ♪

1:31:55.552 --> 1:32:01.099
♪ Got each other
and that's a lot for love..." ♪

1:32:01.183 --> 1:32:05.479
- So, Sandra saw Glenn
at Jessica's birthday party,

1:32:05.562 --> 1:32:09.274
and he wanted to know
if I was seeing someone else

1:32:09.358 --> 1:32:12.903
or, if he actually asked me
to be his girlfriend, if I'd say yes.

1:32:13.987 --> 1:32:15.364
And would you?

1:32:15.447 --> 1:32:18.325
♪ Whoa-oh, livin' on a prayer... ♪

1:32:18.408 --> 1:32:20.369
I don't think he'd take me dancing.

1:32:21.411 --> 1:32:23.038
I don't think I'd take him dancing.

1:32:23.121 --> 1:32:25.082
Happy birthday! It's her birthday!

1:32:25.165 --> 1:32:27.167
-It's her birthday!

1:32:32.130 --> 1:32:36.343
Um, did you mean what you said about

1:32:36.426 --> 1:32:38.303
giving up everything you wanted for me?

1:32:38.387 --> 1:32:41.056
I'm so sorry I said that.

1:32:41.139 --> 1:32:43.141
Of course I didn't mean it.

1:32:45.018 --> 1:32:47.271
I think you did.

1:32:47.354 --> 1:32:49.898
Which is stupid.

1:32:49.982 --> 1:32:52.734
Okay, up next, we have Maxwell Park!

1:32:53.777 --> 1:32:55.153
Come on up, man.

1:32:58.198 --> 1:32:59.449
No, you didn't.

1:32:59.533 --> 1:33:01.994
-No.
-Look, you said you're too tired to drive,

1:33:02.077 --> 1:33:03.996
and-and the highway patrol
took away my permit,

1:33:04.079 --> 1:33:08.959
so I'm not driving anywhere tonight
or in the next six months, so come on.

1:33:09.042 --> 1:33:10.502
Why'd you think I wanted to come here?

1:33:10.585 --> 1:33:12.045
I thought it was the cheese fries.

1:33:12.129 --> 1:33:13.672
Don't be a weenie.

1:33:13.755 --> 1:33:14.965
"Don't be a weenie"?

1:33:15.048 --> 1:33:16.216
Did you not hear their Bon Jovi?

1:33:16.300 --> 1:33:18.385
This is not Broadway.

1:33:20.804 --> 1:33:22.264
All right, Wally Park.

1:33:22.347 --> 1:33:24.349
You better have picked something good.

